@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About the Simulation";
}

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-10 mx-auto">
            <h1 class="mb-4">About the Nuclear War Simulation</h1>
            
            <div class="alert alert-info">
                <h5>🎓 Educational Purpose</h5>
                <p class="mb-0">
                    This simulation is designed as an educational tool to help people understand the devastating 
                    consequences of nuclear weapons. It is not intended to glorify violence or warfare, but rather 
                    to promote awareness and support for nuclear disarmament efforts.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="row mt-4">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h3>🔬 Scientific Basis</h3>
                    <p>
                        The calculations used in this simulation are based on scientifically accepted formulas 
                        from sources including:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>"The Effects of Nuclear Weapons" by Samuel Glasstone and Philip Dolan</li>
                        <li>Declassified nuclear testing data</li>
                        <li>Published academic research on nuclear weapon effects</li>
                        <li>Historical data from Hiroshima and Nagasaki</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                    <h3>📊 What We Calculate</h3>
                    <p>The simulation provides estimates for:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Fireball radius:</strong> Area of complete destruction</li>
                        <li><strong>Radiation zones:</strong> Lethal and harmful radiation areas</li>
                        <li><strong>Blast effects:</strong> Structural damage from overpressure</li>
                        <li><strong>Thermal radiation:</strong> Burns and fire ignition zones</li>
                        <li><strong>Fallout patterns:</strong> Radioactive contamination areas</li>
                        <li><strong>Casualty estimates:</strong> Deaths and injuries based on population density</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-4">
                <h3>⚠️ Important Limitations</h3>
                <div class="alert alert-warning">
                    <p>
                        Please note that this simulation provides estimates based on theoretical calculations. 
                        Real-world effects would vary significantly based on numerous factors including:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="mb-0">
                        <li>Weather conditions and wind patterns</li>
                        <li>Terrain and building structures</li>
                        <li>Exact weapon design and delivery method</li>
                        <li>Time of day and season</li>
                        <li>Emergency response capabilities</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-4">
                <h3>🕊️ Our Mission</h3>
                <p>
                    By providing a realistic visualization of nuclear weapon effects, we hope to:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Educate people about the true scale of nuclear destruction</li>
                    <li>Support efforts toward nuclear disarmament</li>
                    <li>Promote international peace and cooperation</li>
                    <li>Encourage informed public discourse about nuclear policy</li>
                </ul>
                
                <blockquote class="blockquote text-center mt-4">
                    <p class="mb-0">"The unleashed power of the atom has changed everything save our modes of thinking and we thus drift toward unparalleled catastrophe."</p>
                    <footer class="blockquote-footer mt-2">Albert Einstein</footer>
                </blockquote>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
